 <text>
  <front>
   <head>TO A LADY Singing.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">STILL sing, bright Maid, nor cease the pleasing Charm,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Each Soul subdue, each tender Bosom warm;</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Such magick Sweetness to thy Voice is giv'n,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">We hear a Seraph, and we taste of Heav'n:</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Strange force of Harmony, whose Power controuls,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The warring Passions, and informs our Souls,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Soft soothing Sounds, by whose enchantment blest,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Anger and Grief forsake the tranquil Breast;</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">While soft Ideas rising in the Mind,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Bids us in Love a gentle Tyrant find,</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And to his Sway the softned Soul's resign'd.</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Thus sung the  Bard, while all around,</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The list'ning Beasts confess'd the magick Sound:</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Less sweet the Harmony  made,</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">When dancing Stones mov'd to the Notes he play'd;</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Or him, who bore by Dolphins to the Shore,</l>
     <l n="17" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Made Winds and Waves confess his magick Pow'r:</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Thou no less pow'rful o'er the Human Mind,</l>
     <l n="19" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">As great a Triumph from thy Songs can find;</l>
     <l n="20" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Love and its pleasing Pains at once inspire,</l>
     <l n="21" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And fix in ev'ry Breast the latent Fire.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
